h3. Issue Summary

Marketplace partner apps are unable to get mappings for {{jira/classic:workflowRule}} namespace, even when app workflow rules are migrated successfully to cloud. This will block the marketplace partner apps from fixing the configuration of migrated app workflow rules.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Run an app migration with JCMA, which migrates one or more workflow transition rules of your app to cloud
 # From your cloud app, retrieve the mappings available in {{jira/classic:workflowRule}} namespace using [get mappings API|[https://developer.atlassian.com/platform/app-migration/rest/api-group-mapping-api/#api-mapping-transferid-page-get]]

h3. Expected Results

Should be able to receive the mappings of migrated app workflow rules in {{jira/classic:workflowRule}} namespace in the format as follows,
{code:java}
{
  {serverWorkflowRuleID}:{cloudWorkflowId}/{cloudWorkflowRuleID}
} {code}
 
h3. Actual Results

Receiving empty mappings for the namespace {{jira/classic:workflowRule}} .
h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
